18.41	Indian_martial_arts	Indian martial arts	India is home to a variety of fighting styles. Various martial arts including Kung Fu were influenced by Indian martial arts which was brought over along with buddhism . In Sanskrit they may be collectively referred to as or . The former is a compound of the words (weapon) and (knowledge), meaning "knowledge of the sword" or "knowledge of weaponry". The latter term derives from the words for bow and knowledge (), literally the "science of archery" in Puranic literature, later applied to martial arts in general The Vishnu Purana text describes dhanurveda as one of the traditional eighteen branches of "applied knowledge" or upaveda.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/17/Balarama_Mural.jpg/150px-Balarama_Mural.jpg
